<br>
I know I lost experience dying afer a duel because the druid I was dueling was fixing to die and loose the duel and decided to take a cheap shot at me as she lost. And yes, she knew better than to use DoT's in a duel, her main is a Cleric.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
you only lose exp if you die from the dot after the dot caster is dead, or if you step outa the arena. it's how i keep pansy ass tanks in the arena to fight instead of them running up and smacking me once, and runnin back out.<br>
<br>
the basic deal is if you /duel, you won't lose exp from a dot, unless the caster is dead. because when the caster is dead, the system doesn't understand who casted the dot anymore, and that they were dueling with you.<br>
<br>
same with stepping outa an arena. you can't lose exp in an arena death if i'm not mistaken, but if you get dotted and run outside to die, sucks to be you.<br>
<br>
<br>
all in all, dots are a good way to make pansy ass people who hit and run, stay and die. <p>Venerable Jentriken Aspenbark - Permanently Retired<br>
