<br>
There are 2 types of duels, you typing /duel or you whipping ass in the Arena. Arena rules are different.<br>
<br>
Arena rules:<br>
<br>
It's pretty simple. You CANNOT lose ANY xp ANY WAY by dueling in the Arena. You can even die to an NPC inside an Arena and not lose XP. I personally used to hunt my mage around the edges of the Freeport Arena, there was an NPC up there who I used to farm for xp along with the occasional guard, whenever I got adds or something funky happened I jumped in the arena and just let them pound me, boom, no xp loss. The only place this is not true to the best of my knowledge is the Arena in Kael, where people were using the no xp loss rule as an exploit, killing giants in the arena and if you died who cared you lost no XP.<br>
<br>
OK outside arena rules:<br>
<br>
The Dot rumor I honestly cannot say for certain as I have never died due to a DoT or killed someone using our DoT. What I can say is I DO know of one bug. While in ToV a paladin, just having gotten a Windblade, wanted to duel my epic pet. He was lvl 60 and he thought he would whip me for sure. He did not have LoH up. I buffed my pet with BO4, and only gave him a Muzzle. Dueled the pally with JUST the pet, not a single action from me besides sitting there. It was ugly, my pet tore him to shreds, finished the fight at about half life. (BIG tip here, with the new resist changes, BUFF yourself to the gills with resist gear before ANY fight it helps tons) Anyway, when my pet killed him I got this weird message, something like:<br>
<br>
&quot;Your duel cannot continue because your target has died&quot;<br>
<br>
Something like that. Anyway, this had never happened before, every other duel I had cast spells or whatnot on the PC, even when my pet got the killing blow. Oh and the pallly DID lose XP. Some sort of funky pet bug there I suppose. Oh well we had a cleric clicky rezz so it didn't matter too much. <br>
<br>
I'll have to have my necro buddy waste me with DoTs in Arena and outside and see what happens. The amount of XP you lose in 61 is negligible anyway so I don't care much. Will post back when I get some results.<br>
<br>
