<br>
It was after a wipe out in the Oasis <br>
<br>
<br>
We both spawned back in Grobb and where sitting around naked bored waiting for the rezz<br>
<br>
It was so sad to watch neither of us had any points in Hand to Hand and could not hit for more than 2 or 3 points with the odd 10 point kick or slam coming in.<br>
<br>
I only won due to the troll hit point regain and then it was only just<br>
<br>
The sad part is we did this all to the amusement of a Raid killing all the guard. They even had time to bring more people in from out side and start placing bets on us.<br>
<br>
The only other duel i have been that stands out was some smart ass monk trying to KS and nick my spawns when at level 24 i was soloing the lookout room in HHK with my mage.<br>
<br>
The cocky sod tried to /duel me when I was busy trying not to die to his train from one of the lower rooms and I had to gate out.<br>
<br>
But I had bound my self on the 3rd floor in the throne room as it a safe place to recover and not as likely to get trained as the bank.<br>
<br>
When I got back down to the basement after getting my fire pet buffed to hell and back by a passing level 60 guild cleric and shaman I accepted the duel and kicked his ass just by sending the in the pet and watching from the stair well.<br>
<br>
Even with his group trying to heal him it was no contest (hastened monk V DS and uber buffs)<br>
<br>
I just wish I could have dragged his corpse somewhere to hide it but alas VI will not let you do it without the owner consent.<br>
