<br>
I dueled a level 43 Monk friend outside Mistmoore. I started the fight by sending my little doggie pet and landed Togors Insects on him. (Like a 50% slow at the time.) and he was done…<br>
<br>
I let the dog beat on him for a bit, then took my Gatorsmash maul and jumped in to Melee him. I was whacking him for 70’s… we joked about me making a golf tee out of him in the dirt heheh…<br>
<br>
I have a real close Mage friend that I would duel from time to time with my Necro. He is REALLY skilled and beat me the first three times we dueled. I made the mistake of trying to snare and cast other junk… it’s all about the lifetaps though. I’ve learned that.. any Necro that uses a DOT in a Duel is just being mean and inefficient. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
